>
> Notification
>
>
> In an effort to free up disk space,  the ISO will be removing Settlement
> Statement files from the SI Unix machine where SCs currently download
> their settlement statements files from.
>
> Currently, the ISO's SI computer systems have Preliminary Settlements
> Statements (PSS) dating back to January 17th, 1999 and Final Settlements
> Statements (FSS) dating back to January 3rd, 1999 available for SCs to
> download.
>
> On Wednesday, September 1st, 1999 Invoices for the month of June 1999 will
> be produced. On that date, Preliminary Settlement Statements (PSS) prior
> to April 12th, 1999 and Final Settlement Statements (FSS) prior to March
> 29th, 1999 will be removed from the SI computer system and will NOT be
> available for downloading. The CAISO advises all SCs to download
> statements, with dates older than those mentioned above, prior to
> Wednesday if they have not done so already.
>
> Also, effective immediately, the ISO is instituting a policy of charging
> SC's for retrieving statements that have already been removed from the
> system.
>
> A minimum of 90 days worth of statements will be maintained online. After
> statements have been archived and removed from the system, the ISO will
> charge $200 for the first two (2) statements retrieved and $50 for each
> additional statement retrieved.  A "statement" is defined as the statement
> and all of that statement's supplemental files (i.e. the GM, GI, DU & AS
> files). Preliminary and Final Statements are considered two separate
> statements. As an example, if a SC wanted their Preliminary & Final
> Statements for April 1st and 2nd, 1998, they would be charged a total of
> $300.
>
> If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to contact your Client
> Relations Representative.
>
